-- France Beats Italy 30-12 in Opening Game of Rugby’s 6 Nations
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2012-02-04T16:29:24Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-04/france-beats-italy-30-12-in-opening-game-of-rugby-s-6-nations.html
France  defeated  Italy  30-12 in the
opening game of rugby’s 6 Nations championship.  Aurelien Rougerie, Julien Malzieu, Vincent Clerc and Wesley
Fofana touched down as France outscored Italy four tries to none
in extending its winning streak at the Stade de France in Paris
to nine matches. Dimitri Yachvili kicked 10 points for France,
while Kristopher Burton booted 9 points for Italy.  Defending champion England opens its campaign later today
against  Scotland  at Murrayfield in Edinburgh.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  